When we decided to start a family, I knew I wanted to have annual family photos done every year. It’s something I never had growing up, in fact I can only find like 2 photos of my entire family from when I was a kid and I’m only like 3 years old or so. It has always bothered me a little that I didn’t have photos with my mom and dad and all my siblings through the years. So I knew this was something that would be important to me as a mom so that if it was important to my kids they could look back on these photos one day. I still can’t believe these little ones are 2 years old 😭. Our photos came out so good! Especially considering that they are 2 and standing still for photos just does not interest them at all haha. I am so proud of this family of mine 🥰. #familyphotos #triplets #momlife #twomoms #twomomfamily #wlw #momoftriplets

Sometimes there are days we feel guilty for not being able to give our kids the one on one attention they deserve. We never want them to feel like “a package deal” just because they were born on the same day. They will have to share plenty of things including a birthday for the rest of their lives, while that is amazing and they’ll always have that amazing triplet bond we want to celebrate them individually as well, because they are individuals. Being a triplet is one of the least interesting things about these kids. So each year they will get to celebrate their “coming home day”, the day they graduated the NICU and came home with us since they each came home on different days! This year we took advantage of @buildabear ‘s pay their age birthday bear and took the kids on separate days to get their own. We let them pick out their bears outfit all by themselves. We made a whole little “mommy, mama and me date” out of it and took them out to eat at @plantpowerfastfood too! So without further ado…meet Cake-Cake, Chocolaca, and Uni 🧸🧸🧸, our newest triplets lol. Happy Coming Home days babes! Mommy and Mama love you so much and are so proud of the big strong kids you are becoming. (If these bears don’t reflect their individual personalities idk what does 😂) #buildabear #buildabearworkshop #birthdaybear #triplets #nicugraduate #nicugrad #twomoms #twomomsoftriplets

Who are these big kids?! 😭 They are so insanely smart. They kept asking me to make an angle….it took me forever to figure out they wanted this, the nugget put into an angle so they could use it as a slide. They play so well together and are always checking in on each other, helping each other, and looking out for one another. Being their mom is the greatest thing I have ever done. #triplets #momoftriplets

Add taking a break from work in the middle of the morning to spontaneously make the kids cardboard shields and swords to my list of reasons I love being able to be a work from home mom now. A little over a month ago I started the process of getting my insurance license, this brought a lot of new changes to the way our house functions and we are all still adjusting. Last week I actually started my new career after receiving my license and I’ve been loving it. Yes, my days are busy and chaotic as ever, but if anything it has reminded me that when I take that break from work and my focus is 100% on the kids, to slow down. Enjoy that moment, those 5 minutes. Because those moments are creating lifelong memories for these kids and I have the wonderful opportunity to be able to work from home and also be with them day in and day out. It’s encouraged and motivated me to get creative in how we spend time together so that each moment is full of joy, laughter, and bonding. I don’t have to miss these moments just because I’m working again and it makes these memories all the more special now. Grateful for this beautiful life. #workfromhome #workfromhomemom #sfglife #symmetryfinancialgroup #triplets #momoftriplets #lifeinsurance #insurance

“I wish I had done this 30 years ago, it would have saved me a lot of stress and heartache.” - a client I spoke with a few days ago while going over his options for life insurance. 
•
When we are in our 20s and 30s, young, healthy, living our lives to the fullest one of the last things we think about is life insurance. When you’re young, you have this feeling of invincibility. Getting old, dying unexpectedly, getting cancer, becoming disabled suddenly, all feel like such far fetched ideas. While some of us are lucky enough to make it to our 70s in good health, that’s not the case for many and by then, it might be too late. And the truth is…life insurance will not be cheaper for you next year, or the next, or the next. It will never be cheaper than it is right now. 
•
If you have a partner, kids, parents or siblings that would be emotionally and financially impacted or have to set up a GoFundMe if anything were to happen to you (and I’m not just talking about unaliving) to raise money to cover your hospital bills, funeral arrangements, to help take care of your family once you’re gone…we need to talk. Send me a DM or click the link in my bio. Let me help you. ♥️

We have all been sick since we got home from Arizona a week and a half ago. It’s been exhausting. Coughing, crying, fevers, meds, doctors, ear infection, sleepless nights, and never ending snot. 🤒 I’ve spent every night on this couch with at least one kid because they wake up coughing but don’t want to go to “the big bed” AKA mommy and mamas bed but also don’t want to be in their own bed (and I don’t want that either because they will just keep coughing and waking each other up). And slowly through the night, one by one, we all end up here. The four of us, my back on fire, in a cuddle puddle on a corner of the couch. And I pause and think about how one day in the not so distant future this will just be a memory that I get to hold onto, they may not remember these nights, they’re only 2. How they needed my comfort, and each others, and how despite how uncomfortable I am…these are some of my favorite moments. 🥹 They’re still and quiet, as opposed to their usually constant, on the go busy little selves. I can hold them, soak it in, and memorize the tiny details of their faces, their hair. The way their hands subconsciously reach for me and they mumble in their sleep “mommy….” Until they feel me. It’s been a rough week for sure….but it’s also been so much more than that. 🥰 A reminder to yourself: even when things are hard, when you’re exhausted and feel like you aren’t gonna make it or you’re not doing a good enough job….stop. Focus on the good in every moment. Focus on those tiny hands that just want to feel you next to them so they know they’re safe. Focus on the sleepy smile when they wake up and realize you’re still right there. To them…this is everything (and it is to me too) even if they don’t remember it in 10 years. But I will. ♥️ #grateful #blessed #momoftriplets #cuddlepuddle #triplets #motherhood
